To determine this difference, a model (1) was built on the VMR data of larvae at 6 dpf from 1 to 30 s with the following variables: strain (categorical; S), time and its squared term (continuous; t and t
2), their interactions, and random effect of location (γ
i). The time variable was centered to have a mean of zero to reduce the degree of multicollinearity. The squared term of time was included since the log odds of moving larvae proportion were not linear across time. For each strain m (AB, TL, TLAB), we denoted \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
