				\begin{document}$${\beta }_{s}^{(TL)}-{\beta }_{s}^{(AB)}$$\end{document}βs(TL)−βs(AB), describes the average shift in LOA between TL and AB independent of time; whereas the second and third parts indicate how dLOA changed over time.

The fitting results are shown in Table 1, and the corresponding data are plotted in the left panel of Fig. 1. The effect of strain on LOA was decomposed into two parts. The first part was in the main effect. The LOAs of TL and TLAB strains increased by 1.2551 (p < 0.0001) and 0.5601 (p < 0.0001) respectively when compared with that of AB. Thus, more TL and TLAB larvae tended to move when exposed to a Light-On stimulus. In terms of instant behaviour \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
