The larvae displayed substantially different activities by the Light-On and Light-Off stimuli. This difference was quantitatively evaluated by GLMM, using VMR data of AB at 6 dpf from 1 to 30s (i.e. after light change) with the following variables: light stimulus (categorical; L), time and its squared term (continuous; t and t
2), their interactions, and random effect of location (γ
i). For light stimulus l (ON or OFF), we denoted \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
