The VMR data were collected from 3 to 9 dpf, when the larvae were developing. Their maturation would alter the locomotor behaviour14, 31. This developmental difference was modeled by the GLMM, using the VMR data of AB larvae. The model focused on the 1st technical repeat of the Light-On stimulus from 1 to 30 s. It comprised the following variables: stage (categorical; G), time and its squared term (continuous; t and t
2), their interaction s, and random effect of location (γ
i). For stage k (3, …, 9), we denoted \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
